46
00:04:02,133 --> 00:04:04,442
扑克千术的首要规则:
First rule of cheating at cards:

47
00:04:04,933 --> 00:04:06,969
永远掩饰好你的动作
Always cover the move.

48
00:04:08,013 --> 00:04:11,688
说错了.大动作掩护小动作
Misdirection.Big movement covers the small.

49
00:04:12,573 --> 00:04:13,722
很简单的规则
Simple stuff.

50
00:04:14,453 --> 00:04:18,924
还有,如果你可以的话,永远坐在门边
And,if you can,always sit by the door.

51
00:04:30,013 --> 00:04:31,446
- 瞧,Mick - 算了吧
- Look,Mick. - Forget it.

52
00:04:31,533 --> 00:04:34,650
不,我没有打算就此算了,好吗?好吧,我搞砸了
No,I don't want to forget it.All right?Okay,I screwed up.

53
00:04:34,733 --> 00:04:37,122
是啊,你学到了什么?一句话来概括
Yeah,what did you learn?In a sentence.

54
00:04:37,533 --> 00:04:38,932
按照预定的计划来做
Do it by the book.

55
00:04:39,213 --> 00:04:40,248
这边走
This way.

56
00:04:40,333 --> 00:04:43,689
你又搞砸了,Danny 我要把它刺在你的屁股上
You screw up again,Danny,I'll have it tattooed on your ass.

57
00:04:50,213 --> 00:04:53,364
- 这个Frank Gorley是谁? - 魔鬼
- So who's this Frank Gorley? - Beelzebub.

58
00:04:55,373 --> 00:04:57,967
我觉得我们可以以其人之道还治其人之身
I say we give him a taste of his own medicine.

59
00:04:58,173 --> 00:04:59,322
我认识一些人
I know some people.

60
00:04:59,413 --> 00:05:02,166
我可以以人头担保他们能以 任意一种方法来害你
I can personally vouch for how many places they can hurt you.

61
00:05:02,253 --> 00:05:05,131
- 那不是我们要做的 - 那我们要做什么?
- That's not what we do. - What are we gonna do,then?

62
00:05:05,493 --> 00:05:06,562
Ash?
Ash?

63
00:05:14,293 --> 00:05:16,727
他在伦敦西区经营了一家旅馆和赌场
He runs a hotel and casino in the West End.

64
00:05:22,493 --> 00:05:23,721
<i>赌场是他的爱好</i>
<i>The casino's bent.</i>

65
00:05:23,813 --> 00:05:26,771
<i>有人从东欧运送姑娘到他旅馆中</i>
<i>He ships in girls from Eastern Europe for the hotel.</i>

66
00:05:27,573 --> 00:05:32,089
那些船家在赌桌上输掉了他们的钱 只能从匈牙利带姑娘过来
<i>Punters lose their money on the tables,then curl up with Hilda from Hungary.</i>

67
00:05:35,933 --> 00:05:38,447
<i>他不是那种你可以随便对付的人</i>
<i>Not the sort of man you take liberties with.</i>

68
00:05:41,413 --> 00:05:45,292
<i>事实上,如果我们有一份不要去的地方的列表...</i>
<i>In fact,if we had a list of places not to go...</i>

69
00:05:47,573 --> 00:05:49,529
他会列在最上面
he'd be right there at the top.

70
00:05:55,533 --> 00:05:56,761
帮我找出个入口
Find me an in.

71
00:06:09,093 --> 00:06:10,242
和以前一样
The usual.

72
00:06:49,493 --> 00:06:53,088
我就差这一张牌就能成千王之王
I was one card short of a great hand.

73
00:06:53,373 --> 00:06:55,489
或许我应该对你进行宵禁令
Maybe I should put you on a curfew.

74
00:06:57,013 --> 00:06:58,969
你可以试试看啊
I'd like to see you try.

75
00:06:59,173 --> 00:07:02,722
- 你不再是20岁的人了,Albert - 我就是
- You're not 20 years old anymore,Albert. - Yes,I am.

76
00:07:03,253 --> 00:07:06,643
这里,就是这么认为的
Up here,where it counts.

77
00:07:07,093 --> 00:07:10,802
- 你建立了一个非常不好的榜样 - 好吧
- You are setting a very bad example. - Good.

78
00:07:13,693 --> 00:07:16,605
我听说你对小Danny很不好
I hear you're giving young Danny a hard time.

79
00:07:17,653 --> 00:07:18,722
他搞砸了
He screwed up.

80
00:07:20,333 --> 00:07:21,607
我们都搞砸了
We all screw up.

81
00:07:22,253 --> 00:07:25,563
- 所以你接下来才会要考虑作什么 - 或许吧
- It's what you do next that counts. - Maybe.

82
00:07:25,653 --> 00:07:29,851
他有诈骗的天分.你是教不了的
He's got grift sense.You can't teach that.

83
00:07:30,333 --> 00:07:34,212
而且我不会永远在你旁边,你会需要他的
And I'm not gonna be around forever,so you'll need him.

84
00:07:36,453 --> 00:07:40,412
让我来担心Danny吧.你好好休息一下
Let me worry about Danny.You just get some rest.

85
00:07:42,573 --> 00:07:44,165
我们晚一些打电话给你
We'll call back later.

86
00:07:47,293 --> 00:07:49,363
你还需要什么吗,Albie?
Is there anything you want,Albie?

87
00:07:50,013 --> 00:07:53,688
3个护士和一桌的牌
Three nurses and a deck of cards.

88
00:08:02,573 --> 00:08:05,133
我们要回旅馆和Ash碰面.看他找到了什么
We'll meet Ash back at the hotel.See what he's got.

89
00:08:05,213 --> 00:08:06,248
等等
Wait.

90
00:08:10,933 --> 00:08:11,922
给我打电话
Call me.

91
00:08:19,813 --> 00:08:21,166
- Peter? - 什么事?
- Peter? - Yes?

92
00:08:21,253 --> 00:08:23,084
Maureen Phillips,媒体服务的
Maureen Phillips,media services.

93
00:08:23,173 --> 00:08:26,609
- 媒体? - 不好意思.你好
- Media? - Sorry.Hello.

94
00:08:28,413 --> 00:08:29,846
我已经在做了
I'm already on it.

95
00:08:29,933 --> 00:08:33,448
请告诉部长,一切都在掌握之中 他没有什么好担心的
Please tell the Minister it's all in hand.He has nothing to worry about.

96
00:08:33,533 --> 00:08:34,932
我现在就和Peter在一起
I'm with Peter now.

97
00:08:36,293 --> 00:08:37,328
是的
Yeah.

98
00:08:37,413 --> 00:08:40,291
我回去的路上会打电话给你.好的
I'll call you as soon as I'm on my way back.Okay.

99
00:08:40,933 --> 00:08:43,686
对不起.你知道那些政客的嘴脸
Sorry about that.You know what politicians are like.

100
00:08:43,773 --> 00:08:44,922
是啊
Yes.

101
00:08:45,013 --> 00:08:46,651
事情是这样的,有人对我们泄漏说...
The thing is,we've been tipped off...

102
00:08:46,733 --> 00:08:50,328
新闻局正在深入英国国民健康服务进行调查
that the press are conducting an investigation into NHS Trust services.

103
00:08:50,413 --> 00:08:53,405
- 而这家医院被打上了记号 - 我明白了
- And this hospital's been earmarked. - I see.

104
00:08:53,493 --> 00:08:57,247
他们会选择一个病人并在 整个过程中跟踪他的情况...
They select a patient and follow his progress through the system...

105
00:08:57,333 --> 00:08:59,164
并随时进行报告,直到他离开
debriefing him as and when he leaves.

106
00:08:59,253 --> 00:09:01,005
这件事情...
Well,the thing is...

107
00:09:01,093 --> 00:09:03,402
他们选的那个病人是个老头儿...
The patient they've selected is an elderly man...

108
00:09:03,493 --> 00:09:07,168
叫Albert Stroller?
called Albert Stroller?

109
00:09:08,093 --> 00:09:10,163
上帝,我现在似乎就能看到报纸的标题了
God,I can just see the headlines now.

110
00:09:10,253 --> 00:09:12,483
好的,瞧,我会马上着手...
Right,look,I'll get onto it...

111
00:09:12,573 --> 00:09:15,212
找到他,Peter,像对待王子般对待他
Find him,Peter,treat him like a prince.

112
00:09:17,133 --> 00:09:18,964
我们现在可都靠你了
We're all in your hands,now.

113
00:09:31,733 --> 00:09:33,007
谢谢
Thank you.

114
00:09:50,373 --> 00:09:52,204
如果我们一旦需要Albert...
If ever we needed Albert...

115
00:09:53,533 --> 00:09:55,410
即使有入口,我也找不到
If there is an in,I can't find it.

116
00:09:55,493 --> 00:09:58,053
瞧,我们知道他玩牌
Well,look,we know he plays cards.

117
00:09:58,253 --> 00:10:00,323
我们也知道他能发现千术
We also know he can spot a cheat.

118
00:10:00,653 --> 00:10:01,688
女人?
Women?

119
00:10:01,773 --> 00:10:05,129
他有两打妓女可以随时使用,24除以7 但从来没有靠近过她们
He's got two dozen hookers on tap,2<i>4/</i>7,but doesn't go near them.

120
00:10:05,213 --> 00:10:08,205
我跟赌场的某个管理人员聊了一会儿.这个家伙很不合群
I spoke to one of the croupiers at the casino.The guy's a loner.

121
00:10:08,293 --> 00:10:10,124
他每天晚上都把自己锁在房间里面
He locks himself in his room every night.

122
00:10:10,213 --> 00:10:11,487
- 没有朋友? - 没有,什么也没有
- No friends? - No,nothing.

123
00:10:11,573 --> 00:10:13,086
- 亲戚,股东? - 不相信他们
- Stocks,shares? - Doesn't trust them.

124
00:10:13,173 --> 00:10:15,164
一朝被蛇咬,十年怕井绳 发誓再也不会相信了
Dabbled once,lost heavily.Vowed never again.

125
00:10:15,253 --> 00:10:17,403
这家伙斤斤计较,一毛不拔
The man's a block of ice.He calculates the odds.

126
00:10:17,493 --> 00:10:19,324
他永远不会担一点风险
He never goes out on a limb.

127
00:10:19,933 --> 00:10:24,165
至少我所能看见的他唯一 热爱的事情,就是极端地暴力
The only thing he's passionate about,as far as I can see,is extreme violence.

128
00:10:25,573 --> 00:10:27,529
有一件事情
There is one thing.

129
00:10:28,573 --> 00:10:30,882
他总是随身携带笔记本电脑
He carries a laptop wherever he goes.

130
00:10:32,493 --> 00:10:36,532
如果他有弱点的话,这是我们唯一 可以从中发现的地方
If he has got a weakness,that's where we'll find it.

131
00:10:38,333 --> 00:10:41,848
<i>很好,能给Danny一个机会来向我们 展示他学到了多少</i>
<i>Good,it'll give Danny a chance to show us how much he's learned.</i>

132
00:10:54,613 --> 00:10:55,807
我们怎么做?
How we doing?

133
00:10:57,493 --> 00:10:59,563
就看我们花在布局上的精力和时间了
Depends how much we spend on the set up.

134
00:10:59,653 --> 00:11:02,372
不管怎么样,他都惹到了Albert
Whatever it takes.He put his hands on Albert.

135
00:11:03,413 --> 00:11:07,008
但我在书上看到说 "永远不要让你的情感控制理智"
But I thought the book says,"Never let your heart rule your head."

136
00:11:13,173 --> 00:11:14,288
你好?
Hello?

137
00:11:17,893 --> 00:11:19,167
你妻子
Your wife.

138
00:11:36,693 --> 00:11:38,331
我觉得没用
I don't think it works.

139
00:11:39,053 --> 00:11:40,122
什么?
What?

140
00:11:40,213 --> 00:11:42,443
从硬盘上下载下来的东西中进行感应
Downloading from the hard disk telepathically.

141
00:11:42,533 --> 00:11:45,764
- 我还在想 - 但他们已经在吃甜点了
- I'm thinking. - But they're on dessert.

142
00:11:53,093 --> 00:11:55,687
各个击破
Divide and conquer.

143
00:12:04,213 --> 00:12:07,603
打搅一下,你丢了把叉子
Excuse me,you dropped a fork there.

144
00:12:27,613 --> 00:12:28,728
好玩吗?
Having fun?

145
00:12:29,613 --> 00:12:31,331
会让你自然放松
That's a natural laxative.

146
00:12:31,693 --> 00:12:34,651
- 什么?眼药水? - 是的,就看着吧
- What?Eye drops? - Yeah,just watch.

147
00:13:11,293 --> 00:13:14,649
- 我以为你不能忍受这个地方 - 我不能
- I thought you couldn't stand this place. - I can't.

148
00:13:17,973 --> 00:13:19,929
那这一定非常重要
Then it must be important.

149
00:13:20,533 --> 00:13:22,808
Stacie告诉过你我来看你了吗?
Did Stacie tell you I came to see you?

150
00:13:24,253 --> 00:13:26,721
- 她为什么不呢? - 你没有打电话
- Why wouldn't she? - You didn't call.

151
00:13:26,813 --> 00:13:28,041
我很忙的
I've been busy.

152
00:13:29,893 --> 00:13:32,407
- 你看起来不错 - 是不错
- You look well. - I am.

153
00:13:35,093 --> 00:13:38,290
- 谢谢你的信 - 我没有什么好说的
- Thanks for the letters. - I had nothing to say.

154
00:13:46,613 --> 00:13:50,811
我要离婚.没什么的
I want a divorce.Nothing else.

155
00:13:52,173 --> 00:13:55,609
表格只需要一个签名 我曾经邮寄过给你
The forms just need a signature.I even put a stamp on for you.

